`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `scopedRNG` combines scope + worldSeed + extra args via `hashString(key)` → deterministic. Same inputs always → same pseudo-random sequence.
- Cumulative probability selection (weighted roulette wheel) is the standard approach for normalized weights — iterate and pick when `roll < cumulative`.
- A single-branch short-circuit is important: when there's only one option, no RNG call needed (and avoids edge case with weight normalization returning 1.0).
